                                              Monster Hunter World:Iceborne Mod Manager Command Line Tool

Why am I write this application?
        Just interesting.

User Interface :
        > mhwimmc
        mhwimmc: Monster Hunter World:Iceborne Mod Manager
        mhwimmc: cd [ path ]
        mhwimmc: ls
        mhwimmc:
                file
                file
                ...
        mhwimmc: install [ mod name ] [ mod path | mod full path]
        mhwimmc: uninstall [ mod name ]
        mhwimmc: installed
                <mod name> <mod path> <date>
                ...
        mhwimmc: exit

Mod records :
        sqlite table records.
        [ MOD NAME ] [ MOD PATH ] [ DATE ]
        <mod name>   <mod path>   <date>

Modules :
        [ UI Module ]
        [ Command Module ]
        [ Database Module ]

    UI Module :
            UI module handles console message printing and read user input,send the
            input to Command Module

    Command Module :
            Command module receives the input from UI module,parses and process
            the corresponding functions,send command output back to UI module
            Command module also have to take charge of database control,if the command
            install/uninstall a mod,the corresponding database record term must be
            added or removed

    Database Module :
            Database module primaryly handles the database operations
            if Command module need to modify database or retrieve some records,
            it send a message to this module,and thus this module must responses
            the request from Command module

Commands :
        cd => change current work directory
                cd [ path ]
        ls => list current directory
                ls
        install => install a mod
                install [ mod name ] [ mod path ]
                /* mod must not be compressed */
        uninstall => uninstall a mod
                uninstall [ mod name ]
        installed => print all installed mods
                installed
        config => modify a config term
                config [ key ]=[ value ]
                @value: string value
                config without key=value prints all config term
                /* value unspecified config term will has the value "nil" */
        exit => exit program

Config :
        USERHOME => the user's home who first initialized this application
        MHWIROOT => root directory of Monster Hunter World:Iceborne
        MHWIMMCROOT => root directory of mhwimmc

Config handling :
        Command module have to handles program config
        the command "config" is used to modify a config term

Threaded :
        three threads >
                1> UI Module
                2> Command Module
                3> Database Module
        ! all threads are non-detach

        thread synchronization >
                mutex :
                  1> mutex @ucmutex for synchronization between UI and Command
                  2> mutex @cdbmutex for synchronization between Command and Database
                process memory space :
                  1> UI input and Command msg buffer
                     - 
                       struct uc_msg_exchange {
                               status_code
                               io_buffer
                       } ucmsgexchg
                  2> Command and Database msg buffer
                     - 
                       struct table record {
                               database op
                               mod name
                               mod install path
                               install date
                       } cdbmsgexchg

Program exit :
        a global indicator named @program_exit is introduced for tell each threads
        should stop and exit

Signals :
        SIGINT => set @program_exit to TRUE
        SIGTERM => set @program_exit to TRUE

Development Environment :
        Language >
                C and C++
        Compiler >
                gcc 10.3.0 and g++ 10.3.0
        GNU/libc >
                glibc 2.31
        Linux >
                linux 5.4.32
        Sqlite >
                sqlite 3
